title: Polarization of 0.4, 0.7 and 1.0 MeV neutrons scattered by intermediate and heavy nuclei

x4codes.hlp: Atomic Energy Research Establishment (AERE), Harwell, United Kingdom

x4freetext: Polarization of 0.4, 0.7 and 1.0 MeV neutrons
scattered by intermediate and heavy nuclei

x4codes.hlp: Atomic Energy Research Establishment (AERE), Harwell, United Kingdom

x4freetext: 5 MeV Van de Graaff.
Protons incident on Li3-n target of thickness
90 keV.
.Rectangular scatterers, 1.9 cm x 3.2 cm x 7.5 cm,
placed at 50 degr. to the incident proton beam.
Direct detection of elastically scattered
neutrons to determine left-right asymmetry.
Pulse shape discrimination to separate
background gammas.
Two stilbene scintillators placed at 55. degr.
to the left and right of the scatterer.
.Spurious asymmetries eliminated by passing incident
beam through collimator formed by pole faces of an
electromagnet and combining measurements made with
field on and off.
.No corrections made for multiple scattering effects.
Statistical errors are given. No allowance made
for uncertainties in incident neutron polarization.
Table 1 from NP,76,369,1966
